# Refine Early-Stop Breakout Logic

The current 70% duplication breakout logic incorrectly includes VIP/Prioritized listings in the hit-rate calculation. Since VIP listings are often pinned or re-pushed, they can appear as "duplicates" across multiple days, triggering a premature exit even when new "Normal" listings might exist on deeper pages.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change will likely increase the crawl depth for some sessions (potentially hitting more pages) because the "70% dup" barrier is now harder to trigger when VIPs are present. This should result in capturing more "Normal today" listings that were previously missed.

## Proposed Changes

### Spiders

---

#### [MODIFY] [batdongsan.py](file:///d:/Programming/real-estork/spiders/batdongsan.py)

Update `fetch_listings` loop:
- Track `page_normal_count` and `page_normal_dedup_hit` separately from VIP.
- Calculate the breakout ratio based ONLY on Normal listings.
- Ensure that if a page contains only VIP listings, the duplication-based breakout is not triggered.

#### [MODIFY] [muaban.py](file:///d:/Programming/real-estork/spiders/muaban.py)

Update `fetch_listings` loop (similar to Batdongsan):
- Isolate duplication counting to `is_vip=False` listings.
- Adjust the breakout condition to use the Normal listing duplication rate.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- I will perform a dry-run of the logic (manual code review and trace) to ensure the counters are incremented correctly.
- Since live crawling depends on Cloudflare bypasses and real data, validation will primarily be through log inspection once deployed.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that `logger.info` output for each page correctly shows the separated counts (e.g., "Normal dups: X/Y").
- Observe if the spider now crawls beyond page 1/2 when those pages are dominated by old VIP listings.
